              "text_MeeGAc": {
                "type": "text",
                "name": "Text",
                "settings": {
                  "visibility": "always-display",
                  "text": "<p>In my years covering neuro-tech, I’ve seen plenty of \"hacks\"—from high-dose nootropics to extreme polyphasic sleep schedules that leave people looking like ghosts. But recently, a quiet shift occurred in the bio-hacking community. People started appearing more alert, more creative, and strangely, having \"more hours in the day\" than is physically possible. The secret isn't a drug or a diet; it's a fundamental shift in how we perceive—and utilize—the recovery state.</p>",
