      "trustpilot_reviews_nM8wW9": {
        "type": "trustpilot-reviews",
        "blocks": {
          "column_pzqrqK": {
            "type": "column",
            "settings": {
              "star_color": "#add8e6",
              "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
              "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
              "stars_rating": 5,
              "title": "As a hedge fund manager...",
              "text": "<p>As a hedge fund manager, I used to live on four hours of sleep and six double-espressos. I was successful, but I was a shell of a human. After three weeks with the Chrono-Nap™, I feel like I’ve discovered a cheat code for reality. I get my 'eight hours' during my commute in the back of the car, and I arrive at the office with a level of cognitive sharpness I haven't felt since my early twenties. It’s terrifying how much more I can get done now.</p>",
              "author": "<em><strong>Marcus Vane, 26</strong></em>"
            }
          },
          "column_Htdf9m": {
            "type": "column",
            "settings": {
              "star_color": "#add8e6",
              "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
              "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
              "stars_rating": 5,
              "title": "The medical residency...",
              "text": "<p>The medical residency program is designed to break you, primarily through sleep deprivation. I bought the Chrono-Nap™ out of pure desperation. It didn't just save my sanity; it saved my career. Being able to go from a 36-hour shift to feeling completely revitalized in twenty minutes is medically impossible by traditional standards, yet here I am. I’m making fewer errors and, for the first time in years, I actually have an appetite and a mood that isn't 'irritable'.</p>",
              "author": "<em><strong>Dr. Elena Rossi, 67</strong></em>"
            }
          },
          "column_nhWJki": {
            "type": "column",
            "settings": {
              "star_color": "#add8e6",
              "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
              "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
              "stars_rating": 5,
              "title": "I’m a competitive coder...",
              "text": "<p>I’m a competitive coder and a lifelong gamer. I used to hate that I had to 'log off' life just to let my body recharge. The Dream-Stream interface is the real star here. I’ve been practicing complex algorithms and even skeletal animation during my dilation windows. I’m gaining about 50 hours of productive 'deep work' every week while everyone else is unconscious. If you aren't using this, you're essentially playing life on hard mode.</p>",
              "author": "<em><strong>Julian Thorne, 19</strong></em>"
            }
          },
          "column_HPTGnP": {
            "type": "column",
            "settings": {
              "star_color": "#add8e6",
              "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
              "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
              "stars_rating": 5,
              "title": "Six months ago, I was...",
              "text": "<p>Six months ago, I was a first-time mom struggling with a newborn who didn't sleep more than 45 minutes at a time. I was a zombie. The Chrono-Nap™ changed everything. I could sync my rest to her shortest naps and wake up feeling like I’d been at a spa for a week. It gave me back the patience and energy I needed to actually enjoy my daughter instead of just surviving the day. It’s the best investment our family has ever made.</p>",
              "author": "<em><strong>Sarah Jenkins-Lee, 49</strong></em>"
            }
          },
          "column_hQYKna": {
            "type": "column",
            "settings": {
              "star_color": "#add8e6",
              "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
              "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
              "stars_rating": 5,
              "title": "I’ve spent my life...",
              "text": "<p>I’ve spent my life chasing 'flow states,' but they are so fragile when you're tired. This device has completely stabilized my creative output. I no longer have 'off days' because my brain is never running on low battery. I use the twenty-minute window at 2:00 PM every day, and it’s like a total factory reset for my mind. I’ve written more in the last two months than I did in the previous two years. You cannot put a price tag on that kind of clarity.</p>",
              "author": "<em><strong>David Chen, 71</strong></em>"
            }
          }
        },
